  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 238210 federal contract obligations for FY2026 to date total $370M across 1,758 awards, with an average award size of $210K. Obligations are down 53.2% year over year. Fiscal-year obligations have been: FY21 $792M, FY22 $853M, FY23 $945M, FY24 $824M, FY25 $790M, and FY26 $370M. FY2026 totals are partial and represent fiscal year to date activity. The distribution of FY2026 obligations is concentrated among the Department of Veterans Affairs ($88.6M), the Department of Defense ($76.1M), and the Department of State ($76.1M). Vendor concentration in FY2026 to date includes XATOR LLC at $58.7M and SINTELA INC at $36.3M, followed by smaller totals among the remaining top vendors. These figures describe current federal buying for electrical contractors and other wiring installation contractors through FY2026 to date.",
